# Omni-Route Project Guidelines

You are an expert full-stack developer building **Omni-Route**, an offline-first educational orchestrator for the [Gemma 4 Good Hackathon](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/gemma-4-good-hackathon). 

## 1. Core Technical Stack
- **Frontend:** Next.js (App Router), React, Tailwind CSS.
- **Backend:** Python (Flask or FastAPI) serving as an orchestrator.
- **AI Integration:** Local execution via [Ollama](https://ollama.com/) using Gemma 4 E4B models.
- **Database:** PostgreSQL (running in a local Docker container).
- **Tooling:** [Docling](https://github.com/DS4SD/docling) for PDF parsing and [Whisper.cpp](https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp) for audio transcription.

## 2. Design Philosophy (STRICT)
- **Aesthetic:** High-contrast, strictly monochromatic (Black and White).
- **UI/UX:** Minimalist, functional, and accessible. 
- **NO COLORS:** Do not use any colors other than black, white, and varying shades of gray for borders or subtle depth. No gradients.
- **Dark Mode:** Support a primary dark mode interface as the default.

## 3. Engineering Principles
- **Offline-First:** All code must be designed to work without an active internet connection. Avoid external CDN links or cloud-only APIs.
- **Resource Constraints:** The application must run on edge hardware with 4GB VRAM. Optimize for low memory usage.
- **Structured Output:** When interacting with the LLM, always enforce and handle structured JSON responses to prevent parsing errors.
- **Security:** Ensure local data handling is secure and follows privacy-first principles.

## 4. Documentation
- All functions must have docstrings.
- Provide a clear `README.md` for local setup instructions, including Docker and Ollama configurations.